/PATCHSET_LEVEL.message:
Sorry, but I  don't like this approach, and I refer back to my previous comment that it's misleading to use $::os_service_default when cinder doesn't provide a default value. FWIW, cinder is highly unlikely to change the netapp_copyoffload_tool_path option.

If the goal is to avoid adding empty values to cinder.conf then how about something like this:

  if $netapp_copyoffload_tool_path != undef {
    cinder_config {
      "${name}/netapp_copyoffload_tool_path": value => $netapp_copyoffload_tool_path;
    }
  }

I think that would also continue to work in the unlikely event that cinder *does* switch to using an actual default value.

> I'm afraid I've not yet fully understood your concerns.
> 
> For netapp_copyoffload_tool_path option, no default value is defined by oslo.config interface, which makes the parameter "default to None". The current netapp driver treats None and '' in the same manner, and disables copyoffload feature for both these values.

I agree.

> The current default is just redundant because it always sets the optional parameter, in a wired format which eventually results in service default.

I think you're saying the current code (which this patch would modify) sets an empty/blank value "netapp_copyoffload_tool_path=" which I agree is redundant and undesirable.

> > If the goal is to avoid adding empty values to cinder.conf then how about something like this:
> 
> I don't agree with this. This eventually results in missing netapp_copyoffload_tool_path, which is effectively same as the current change, and leaves the parameter unmanaged if a user set the parameter once but remove that later.

This could work:

  if $netapp_copyoffload_tool_path == undef {
    cinder_config {
      "${name}/netapp_copyoffload_tool_path": ensure => absent;
    }
  } else {
    cinder_config {
      "${name}/netapp_copyoffload_tool_path": value => $netapp_copyoffload_tool_path;
    }
  }

But it's also getting rather unwieldy, and I'm starting to rethink my objection to using $::os_service_default for the default value. I'll take a few minutes to think about it while we wait for CI results.

Try this:

  ['netapp_vserver', 'netapp_copyoffload_tool_path'].each |String $netapp_opt| {
    $netapp_val = getvar("${netapp_opt}")
    if $netapp_val == undef {
      cinder_config {
        "${name}/${netapp_opt}": ensure => absent;
      }
    } else {
      cinder_config {
        "${name}/${netapp_opt}": value => $netapp_val;
      }
  }

