nit: fstring shouldn't be used with logger functions, since they looks basically like this:

  def info(msg, *args):
      if isEnabledFor(INFO):
          print(msg % args)

so the msg string will be interpolated with values only when needed, depending on the log level.

logscraper/logsender.py.message:
I think you can achieve a similar result with this dependency-free implementation:

    timestamp_patterns = [
        # Mar 25 17:40:37
        (re.compile(r"(\S+ \S+ \S_)"), "%b %d %H:%M:%S"),
        # 2022-03-25T17:40:37
        (re.compile(r"(\S+)"), "%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S"),
        # 2022-03-25
        (re.compile(r"(\S+)"), "%Y-%m-%d"),
    ]


    def get_timestamp(line):
        for (regex, fmt) in timestamp_patterns:
            try:
                if match := regex.match(line):
                    timestamp_string = match.groups()[0].rstrip('Z')
                    return datetime.datetime.strptime(timestamp_string, fmt)
            except ValueError:
                pass

